# Data Science Journey

## ETL
- Extract
- Transform
- Load

### Extract

### Transform
- on the back-end: incorrect data, corrupt data, missing data
- Outlier and missing value detection and handling
  - detect by distribution curve or other plots
  - replace them by mean or median values
  - introduce a dummy variable whether data is missing or not

#### Convert values
- default date format: yyyy-mm-dd
- default currency: xx.xx MU

### Load to database / datawarehose
- check number of rows (top & bottom)
- check value types (dates and currencies)
- check text values

## Analysis
- regression
- classification (eg. decision tree/random forest, K-Nearest Neighbor, Naive Bayes, log regression)
- clustering (eg. kmeans, hierarchical clustering)
- reinforment learning (exploration & explotation, eg. multi-armed bandit problem, upper-confidence bound algorithm UCB, Thompson sampling)
- neural networks and deep learning

## Data visualisation


## Presentation
- How to present insights, communicate and organize in simple teams
- (Receiver-Directed) Communication: Kommunikation ist nicht was gesagt wird, sondern was ankommt. 
- Why? How? What?
- Project Pipeline for Projects: everyone can access the dashboard and post their requests, e.g. Trello Board

- Self-serve analytics: create Summary Tables for the most frequent requests: 
  - Amazon Redshift: https://aws.amazon.com/redshift/?whats-new-cards.sort-by=item.additionalFields.postDateTime&whats-new-cards.sort-order=desc
  - Chartio: https://chartio.com/

